  <exercise>
    <title>Find the p-value, I</title>
    <statement>
      <p>A random sample is selected from an approximately normal population with an unknown standard deviation. Find the p-value for the given sample size and test statistic. Also determine if the null hypothesis would be rejected at <m>\alpha = 0.05</m>.</p>
      <p><ol marker="a.">
        <li><m>n = 11</m>, <m>T = 1.91</m></li>
        <li><m>n = 17</m>, <m>T = -3.45</m></li>
        <li><m>n = 7</m>, <m>T = 0.83</m></li>
        <li><m>n = 28</m>, <m>T = 2.13</m></li>
      </ol></p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <title>Find the p-value, II</title>
    <statement>
      <p>A random sample is selected from an approximately normal population with an unknown standard deviation. Find the p-value for the given sample size and test statistic. Also determine if the null hypothesis would be rejected at <m>\alpha = 0.01</m>.</p>
